On Tue, Jan 5, 2010 at 3:44 PM, Will McAfee <sec-community@...goodhacker.com
> wrote:

> I am an iPhone app developer working on a security toolkit app.  My
> question is simple.  What would you find most useful in a security
> tool app?
>

Some ideas...

/etc/services - searchable list
/etc/protocols - searchable list
subnet/supernet calculator with CIDR
nmap with ability to save results in app as well as email them
nbtstat with ability to save results in app as well as email them
bonjour discovery of hosts on same subnet as phone along with list of
services on each host
http://cve.mitre.org/cve/ <- searchable


